<eesti>Riigivastutuse seadus </eesti>
<inglise>State Liability Act </inglise>
<eesti>Vastu v&otilde;etud 2. mail 2001. a. </eesti>
<inglise>Passed 2 May 2001, </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2001, 47, 260), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT (1) I 2001, 47, 260), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 1. jaanuaril 2002. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 1 January 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus s&auml;testab avaliku v&otilde;imu volituste rakendamisel ja muude avalike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel rikutud &otilde;iguste kaitse ja taastamise ning tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamise alused ja korra (riigivastutus). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the bases of and procedure for the protection and restoration of rights violated upon the exercise of powers of public authority and performance of other public duties and compensation for damage caused (state liability). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolev seadus ei reguleeri &otilde;iguste taastamist ega kahju h&uuml;vitamist era&otilde;iguslikus suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act does not regulate the restoration of rights or compensation for damage in private law relationships. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kahju tekitamisena era&otilde;iguslikus suhtes k&auml;sitatakse kahju tekitamist avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja poolt: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Causing damage in a private law relationship means a public authority causing damage in the following circumstances: </inglise>
<eesti>1) v&otilde;la&otilde;igussuhtest tuleneva kohustuse rikkumisel, sealhulgas era&otilde;iguslikus vormis veo-, ravi- v&otilde;i muu teenuse osutamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon the violation of a prestation, including providing transport services, health services or other services as a person in private law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kinnisasja, tee, veekogu v&otilde;i muu asja omanikuna oma kohustusi, v&auml;lja arvatud liiklusseaduse (RT I 2001, 3, 6) &sect;-s 45 s&auml;testatud kohustusi, rikkudes; </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon the violation of its obligations as the owner of an immovable, road, body of water or another thing, except the obligations provided for in &sect; 45 of the Traffic Act (RT I 2001, 3, 6); </inglise>
<eesti>3) liikluses osalemisel v&otilde;i ohtliku seadme kasutamisel v&otilde;i aine valdamisel, kasutamata avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja eri&otilde;igusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) when participating in traffic or upon the use of dangerous equipment or possession of hazardous substances without exercising the special rights of public authorities; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muul viisil era&otilde;iguslikus vormis tegutsedes. </eesti>
<inglise>4) when acting in another manner as a person in private law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguste kaitse ja taastamise ning kahju h&uuml;vitamise n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Claims for protection and restoration of rights and compensation for damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel v&otilde;ib isik riigilt, kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuselt, muult avalik-&otilde;iguslikult juriidiliselt isikult v&otilde;i muult avalikke &uuml;lesandeid avalik-&otilde;iguslikul alusel v&auml;ljaspool alluvussuhet teostavalt isikult (avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjalt) n&otilde;uda: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the basis of this Act, a person may request that the state, a local government, another legal person in public law or another person performing public duties on a public law basis outside of relationships of subordination (a public authority): </inglise>
<eesti>1) haldusakti t&uuml;histamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) annul an administrative act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;tkuva toimingu l&otilde;petamist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) terminate a continuing measure; </inglise>
<eesti>3) haldusakti andmisest v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamisest hoidumist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) refrain from issuing an administrative act or taking a measure; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haldusakti andmist v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) issue an administrative act or take a measure; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist; </eesti>
<inglise>5) compensate for damage caused; </inglise>
<eesti>6) avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes alusetult saadud asja v&otilde;i raha tagastamist. </eesti>
<inglise>6) return a thing or money received without legal basis in a public law relationship. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seadusega v&otilde;ib isiku &otilde;iguste taastamiseks, kaitseks v&otilde;i kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks ette n&auml;ha t&auml;iendavaid n&otilde;udeid v&otilde;i k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid piirata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Additional claims may be prescribed and claims provided for in this Act may be restricted by law in order to restore or protect the rights of persons or to compensate for damage. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) M&otilde;isteid "haldusakt" ja "toiming" kasutatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses haldusmenetluse seaduse t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In this Act, the terms "administrative act" and "measure" are used within the meaning of the Administrative Procedure Act. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;uded haldusakti v&otilde;i toimingu suhtes </eesti>
<inglise>Claims Regarding Administrative Acts or Measures </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldusakti t&uuml;histamise n&otilde;ue </eesti>
<inglise>Claim for annulment of administrative act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda haldusakti t&uuml;histamist &uuml;ksnes selles ulatuses, milles rikutakse tema &otilde;igusi, kui seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may request the annulment of an administrative act only to the extent that the rights of the person are violated unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Haldusakti t&uuml;histamist ei v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda, kui isiku &otilde;igused on taastatud haldusakti muutmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The annulment of an administrative act shall not be requested if the rights of the person are restored by amendment to the administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Haldusakti t&uuml;histamist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda vaidega haldusmenetluses v&otilde;i kaebusega halduskohtumenetluses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The annulment of an administrative act may be requested by a challenge in administrative proceedings or by an action in administrative court proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Toimingu l&otilde;petamise n&otilde;ue </eesti>
<inglise>Claim for termination of measure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda halduse j&auml;tkuva toiminguga kaasneva &otilde;iguste rikkumise l&otilde;petamist, kui see on v&otilde;imalik &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;raste kuludeta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may request the termination of a violation of rights which results from a continuing administrative measure if the termination is possible without excessive costs. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguste rikkumise l&otilde;petamise kulud on &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;rased, kui need &uuml;letavad oluliselt isikule &otilde;iguste rikkumisega tekitatavat kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>Costs of the termination of a violation of rights are excessive if the costs exceed substantially the damage caused to the person by the violation of rights. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui &otilde;iguste rikkumine seisneb asja &otilde;igusvastases valdamises, v&otilde;ib asja valdamiseks &otilde;igustatud isik n&otilde;uda asja oma valdusesse andmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If unlawful possession of a thing constitutes violation of rights, the entitled possessor of the thing may request the transfer of the thing into his or her possession. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse asja &otilde;igusp&auml;rasesse valdusesse andmiseks v&otilde;ib haldusorganile esitada 30 aasta jooksul n&otilde;ude&otilde;iguse tekkimisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>An application for the transfer of a thing into lawful possession may be submitted to an administrative authority within thirty years as of the creation of the right of claim. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotluse toimingu l&otilde;petamiseks v&otilde;ib esitada toimingut sooritavale haldusorganile v&otilde;i kaebuses halduskohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application for the termination of a measure may be submitted to the administrative authority taking the measure, or a respective action may be filed with an administrative court in an appeal. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldusaktist v&otilde;i toimingust hoidumise n&otilde;ue </eesti>
<inglise>Claim for refrainment from administrative act or measure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda haldusakti andmata j&auml;tmist v&otilde;i halduse toimingu sooritamata j&auml;tmist, kui haldusakt v&otilde;i toiming rikuks tema &otilde;igusi ja tooks t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt endaga kaasa tagaj&auml;rje, mida ei saaks k&otilde;rvaldada haldusakti v&otilde;i toimingu hilisemal vaidlustamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may request that an administrative act be not issued or administrative measure be not taken if the administrative act or measure would violate the rights of the person and would probably bring about consequences which would be impossible to eliminate upon later contestation of the administrative act or measure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taotluse haldusakti andmata j&auml;tmiseks v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamata j&auml;tmiseks v&otilde;ib esitada haldusakti andmiseks v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamiseks p&auml;devale haldusorganile v&otilde;i kaebuses halduskohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A request that an administrative act be not issued or a measure be not taken may be submitted to the administrative authority which is competent to issue the administrative act or take the measure, or a respective action may be filed with an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldusakti andmise v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamise n&otilde;ue </eesti>
<inglise>Claim for issue of administrative act or taking of measure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda haldusakti andmist v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamist, kui avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja on kohustatud haldusakti andma v&otilde;i toimingu sooritama ja see puudutab isiku &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may request the issue of an administrative act or taking of a measure if a public authority is required to issue the administrative act or take the measure and if this concerns the rights of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui haldusakti andmine v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamine tuleb otsustada halduse kaalutlus&otilde;iguse (diskretsiooni) alusel, v&otilde;ib isik n&otilde;uda haldusakti andmist v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamist &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui see puudutab tema &otilde;igusi ja juhtumi asjaolude t&otilde;ttu ei saa haldusorgan haldusakti andmisest v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamisest keelduda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the issue of an administrative act or taking of a measure shall be decided on the basis of the administrative right of discretion (discretion), a person may request the issue of the administrative act or taking of the measure only if this concerns the rights of the person and, due to the specific circumstances, the administrative authority cannot refuse to issue the administrative act or take the measure. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotlus haldusakti andmiseks v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamiseks tuleb esitada selleks p&auml;devale haldusorganile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A request to issue an administrative act or take a measure shall be submitted to a competent administrative authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse rahuldamata v&otilde;i t&auml;htaegselt l&auml;bi vaatamata j&auml;tmise korral v&otilde;ib isik esitada vaide haldusorganile v&otilde;i kaebuse halduskohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>If a request is not granted or not reviewed on time, the person may file a challenge with an administrative authority or an action with an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for Damage </inglise>
<eesti>1. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutuse alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases of liability </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik, kelle &otilde;igusi on avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja &otilde;igusvastase tegevusega avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes rikkunud (edaspidi kannatanu), v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda talle tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist, kui kahju ei olnud v&otilde;imalik v&auml;ltida ega ole v&otilde;imalik k&otilde;rvaldada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 3, 4 ja 6 s&auml;testatud viisil &otilde;iguste kaitsmise v&otilde;i taastamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person whose rights are violated by the unlawful activities of a public authority in a public law relationship (hereinafter injured party) may claim compensation for damage caused to the person if damage could not be prevented and cannot be eliminated by the protection or restoration of rights in the manner provided for in &sect;&sect; 3, 4 and 6 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusetusega tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui haldusakt j&auml;i &otilde;igeaegselt andmata v&otilde;i toiming &otilde;igeaegselt sooritamata ja sellega rikuti isiku &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Compensation for damage caused by a failure to act may be claimed only if an administrative act is not issued in due course or a measure is not taken in due course and the rights of a person are violated thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igete 1 ja 2 alusel h&uuml;vitatakse otsene varaline kahju ja saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Direct proprietary damage and loss of income are compensated for on the basis of subsections (1) and (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui seadusega pole s&auml;testatud teisiti ja see pole vastuolus avalik&otilde;iguslike suhete olemusega, kohaldatakse avaliku v&otilde;imu teostamisel tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamisel lisaks k&auml;esolevale seadusele ka era&otilde;iguse kahju h&uuml;vitamise s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In addition to this Act, the provisions of private law concerning compensation for damage also apply upon the compensation for damage caused in exercising public authority unless otherwise provided by law and if it is not in conflict with the nature of public law relationships. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Varalise kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for proprietary damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Varaline kahju h&uuml;vitatakse rahas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Proprietary damage shall be compensated for in money. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitisega tuleb luua varaline olukord, milles kannatanu oleks siis, kui tema &otilde;igusi ei oleks rikutud. </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation shall create the financial situation in which the injured party would be had his or her rights not been violated. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kehavigastuse tekitamisel v&otilde;i tervise kahjustamisel v&otilde;ib kannatanu n&otilde;uda sellega tekitatud kulutuste h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the injured party suffers a bodily injury or health damage, he or she may claim compensation for expenses caused thereby. </inglise>
<eesti>Sealhulgas v&otilde;ib kannatanu n&otilde;uda j&auml;rgmiste kulutuste h&uuml;vitamist: </eesti>
<inglise>The injured party may also claim compensation for the following expenses: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vajalikud ravikulud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) expenses for necessary medical treatment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) vajaduste suurenemisest tingitud kulud; </eesti>
<inglise>2) expenses caused by increased needs; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu, sealhulgas sissetulekute v&auml;henemisest v&otilde;i edasiste majanduslike v&otilde;imaluste halvenemisest tingitud kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>3) loss of income due to incapacity for work, including damage caused by a decrease in income or worsening of further economic opportunities. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) H&uuml;vitist t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuse t&otilde;ttu saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu eest ei saa n&otilde;uda osas, milles kannatanul on &otilde;igus kahju tekitamisest tulenevalt saada t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuspensioni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Compensation for loss of income due to incapacity for work cannot be claimed to the extent to which the injured party is entitled to pension for incapacity for work due to the damage caused. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) P&uuml;siva terviserikke tekitamisel tuleb kahju h&uuml;vitada perioodiliste rahaliste maksetena iga kolme kuu eest ette. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a permanent health disorder is caused, the damage shall be compensated for by periodic monetary payments payable in advance for every three-month period. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju iseloomu arvestades v&otilde;ib h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramisel v&otilde;i v&auml;ljam&otilde;istmisel seda ajavahemikku muuta v&otilde;i n&auml;ha ette &uuml;hekordse makse. </eesti>
<inglise>Taking into account the nature of damage, this period of time may be altered or a single payment may be prescribed upon the grant or order of payment of compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Mittevaralise kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for non-proprietary damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda mittevaralise kahju rahalist h&uuml;vitamist s&uuml;&uuml;liselt v&auml;&auml;rikuse alandamise, tervise kahjustamise, vabaduse v&otilde;tmise, kodu v&otilde;i eraelu puutumatuse v&otilde;i s&otilde;numi saladuse rikkumise, au v&otilde;i hea nime teotamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A natural person may claim financial compensation for non-proprietary damage upon wrongful degradation of dignity, damage to health, deprivation of liberty, violation of the inviolability of home or private life or the confidentiality of messages or defamation of honour or good name of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Mittevaraline kahju h&uuml;vitatakse proportsionaalselt &otilde;iguserikkumise raskusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Non-proprietary damage shall be compensated for in proportion to the gravity of the offence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju h&uuml;vitamine kolmandatele isikutele </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation of damage to third persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Surma p&otilde;hjustamisel, kehavigastuse tekitamisel v&otilde;i tervise kahjustamisel on kolmandal isikul &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda sellega seoses kantud kulutuste, &auml;ralangenud &uuml;lalpidamise ja mittevaralise kahju h&uuml;vitamist era&otilde;iguses s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the causing of death or a bodily injury or damage to health, a third person is entitled to claim compensation for related expenses incurred, for loss of support and non-proprietary damage on the bases provided by private law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Auml;ralangenud &uuml;lalpidamise h&uuml;vitamist ei saa n&otilde;uda ulatuses, milles kolmandal isikul tekkis surma p&otilde;hjustamisest tulenevalt &otilde;igus saada toitjakaotuspensioni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Compensation for loss of support cannot be claimed to the extent to which the third person is entitled to survivor's pension. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;ralangenud &uuml;lalpidamine h&uuml;vitatakse maksetega sarnaselt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;ikele 4. </eesti>
<inglise>Loss of support shall be compensated for in payments and in a manner similar to that provided for in subsection 8 (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Elimination of consequences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kannatanu v&otilde;ib avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjalt rahalise h&uuml;vitise asemel n&otilde;uda t&uuml;histatud v&otilde;i vastavas osas muudetud haldusakti v&otilde;i toimingu &otilde;igusvastaste tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Instead of financial compensation, an injured party may request from a public authority the elimination of the unlawful consequences of a repealed administrative act or a partially amended administrative act or a measure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja on tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamisel kohustatud rakendama k&otilde;iki &otilde;igusp&auml;raseid abin&otilde;usid, sealhulgas andma haldusakte, sooritama toiminguid v&otilde;i esitama kolmanda isiku vastu era&otilde;iguslikke n&otilde;udeid, kui selleks on olemas &otilde;iguslik alus ja tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamise kulud ei &uuml;letaks oluliselt rahalist h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A public authority is required, upon the elimination of consequences, to take all lawful measures, including the issue of administrative acts, taking of measures and filing of claims in private law against third parties if legal basis therefor exists and if the costs of elimination of consequences would not substantially exceed financial compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja v&otilde;ib, s&otilde;ltumata kannatanu tahtest, k&otilde;rvaldada tagaj&auml;rjed k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud viisil, kui rahaline h&uuml;vitis oleks oluliselt suurem tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamise kuludest ja isikul pole kaalukat p&otilde;hjust n&otilde;uda rahalist h&uuml;vitist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A public authority may, regardless of the request of the injured party, eliminate consequences in the manner provided for in subsection (2) of this section if financial compensation would substantially exceed the costs of the elimination of consequences, unless the person has good reason for claiming financial compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks kohustatud isik </eesti>
<inglise>Person obligated to compensate for damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kahju kannatanud isikule on kahju h&uuml;vitama kohustatud avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja, kelle tegevusega kahju tekitati. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The public authority whose activities caused damage is required to compensate the injured person for the damage. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusetusega tekitatud kahju on kohustatud h&uuml;vitama avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja, kes j&auml;ttis &otilde;igeaegselt haldusakti andmata v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamata. </eesti>
<inglise>The public authority who fails to issue an administrative act or take a measure in due course is required to compensate for damage caused by the failure to act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja poolt tekitatud kahjuks loetakse igasugune selle avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itnud f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt vahetult p&otilde;hjustatud kahju, s&otilde;ltumata sellest, kas &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;ideti teenistussuhte, lepingu, &uuml;ksikkorralduse v&otilde;i muul alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Any damage caused directly by a natural person performing the functions of a public authority, regardless of whether the functions are performed on the basis of a service relationship, contract, single order or on another basis, is deemed to be damage caused by the public authority. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes nimetatud f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik kannatanu ees ei vastuta, kui seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>Natural persons specified in this subsection are not liable to the injured party unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) F&uuml;&uuml;silisest v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslikust juriidilisest isikust avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja poolt tekitatud kahju eest vastutab riik, kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus v&otilde;i muu avalik-&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik, kes andis f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslikule juriidilisele isikule volitused avalike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks, kui seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If damage is caused by a public authority who is a natural person or private law legal person, the state, local government or other public law legal person who authorised the natural person or private law legal person to perform public duties is liable for the damage unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui kahju on kohustatud h&uuml;vitama mitu avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjat, vastutavad nad kannatanu ees solidaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If several public authorities are obligated to compensate for damage, the public authorities are solidarily liable to the injured party. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja osa ei saa solidaarvastutuse korras n&otilde;uda isikult, kes vastutab kannatanu ees era&otilde;igusest tulenevalt. </eesti>
<inglise>Solidary liability of a public authority shall not extend to a person who is liable to the injured party under private law. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamiseks vajaliku haldusakti andmine v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamine ei ole k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja p&auml;devuses, on tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamiseks vajaliku haldusakti v&otilde;i toimingu kohustatud andma v&otilde;i sooritama p&auml;dev avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the issue of an administrative act or taking of a measure necessary for the elimination of consequences is not within the competence of the public authority specified in subsection (1) of this section, a competent public authority is obligated to issue the administrative act or take the measure necessary for the elimination of the consequences. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutuse piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restriction of liability </inglise>
<eesti>(1) H&uuml;vitise suuruse m&auml;&auml;ramisel arvestatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following shall be taken into account upon determining the amount of compensation: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kahju tekkimise etten&auml;gematust; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the extent to which the damage was unforeseeable; </inglise>
<eesti>2) objektiivseid takistusi kahju &auml;rahoidmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) objective obstacles to preventing damage; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;iguste rikkumise raskust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) gravity of the violation of rights; </inglise>
<eesti>4) era&otilde;iguses s&auml;testatud piiranguid seoses kannatanu osaga kahju tekitamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) restrictions in connection with the part the injured party had in causing the damage which are provided for in private law; </inglise>
<eesti>5) muid asjaolusid, millest tulenevalt kahju h&uuml;vitamine t&auml;ies ulatuses oleks eba&otilde;iglane. </eesti>
<inglise>5) other circumstances which would render compensation for damage in full unfair. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu ei h&uuml;vitata, kui kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks kohustatud isik t&otilde;endab, et ta ei olnud kahju tekitamises s&uuml;&uuml;di. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Loss of income is not compensated for if the person liable to compensate for the damage proves that the person is not at fault in causing the damage. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja vabaneb vastutusest avalike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel tekitatud kahju eest, kui kahju tekitamist ei olnud v&otilde;imalik v&auml;ltida ka avalike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel vajalikku hoolsust t&auml;ielikult j&auml;rgides. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A public authority shall be relieved of liability for damage caused in the course of performance of public duties if the damage could not have been prevented even if diligence necessary for the performance of public duties had been fully observed. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamist n&otilde;udev kannatanu on kohustatud kandma tagaj&auml;rgede k&otilde;rvaldamise kulud ulatuses, mis vastab tema osale tagaj&auml;rgede tekitamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An injured party who requests the elimination of consequences is required to bear the costs of elimination of consequences to the extent corresponding to the part the injured party had in causing the consequences. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tagaj&auml;rjed j&auml;&auml;vad k&otilde;rvaldamata seet&otilde;ttu, et kannatanul ei ole v&otilde;imalik oma osale vastavaid kulusid kanda, v&otilde;ib ta n&otilde;uda rahalist h&uuml;vitist avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja osale vastavas ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>If consequences are not eliminated because the injured party cannot bear the costs corresponding to the part the injured party had in causing the damage, the injured party may request financial compensation corresponding to the share of liability of the public authority. </inglise>
<eesti>2. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutuse erijuhud </eesti>
<inglise>Special cases of liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igustloova aktiga tekitatud kahju </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused by legislation of general application </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda &otilde;igustloova aktiga tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui &otilde;igustloova aktiga rikuti oluliselt tema &otilde;igusi ja Riigikohus on tunnistanud vastava s&auml;tte kehtetuks v&otilde;i p&otilde;hiseadusevastaseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may claim compensation for damage caused by legislation of general application only if the rights of the person were materially violated by the legislation of general application and the Supreme Court has repealed the corresponding provision of law or declared it unconstitutional. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;igustloova akti t&otilde;ttu saamata j&auml;&auml;nud tulu v&otilde;i sellega tekitatud mittevaraline kahju, samuti seadusega v&otilde;i &otilde;igustloova akti andmata j&auml;tmisega tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitatakse &uuml;ksnes eraldi seaduses s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Loss of income as a result of legislation of general application or non-proprietary damage caused thereby and damage caused by an Act or failure to issue legislation of general application are only compensated for in cases provided for in a separate Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ige 1 ei v&auml;lista vastutust &otilde;igustloova akti alusel antud haldusakti v&otilde;i sooritatud toiminguga tekitatud kahju eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Subsection (1) of this section does not preclude liability for damage caused by an administrative act issued or measure taken on the basis of legislation of general application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtumenetluse ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise kohtuv&auml;lise arutamise k&auml;igus tekitatud kahju </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused in course of judicial proceedings and extrajudicial hearing of matters concerning administrative offences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda kohtumenetluse v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise kohtuv&auml;lise arutamise k&auml;igus, sealhulgas kohtulahendiga v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas tehtud lahendiga tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist &uuml;ksnes juhul, kui kohtunik v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja kohtuv&auml;liselt arutanud ametiisik pani selle menetluse k&auml;igus toime kuriteo. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may claim compensation for damage caused in the course of judicial proceedings or extrajudicial hearing of a matter concerning an administrative offence, including damage caused by a court decision or a decision made in the matter of an administrative offence, only if a judge or the official who extrajudicially heard the matter of administrative offence committed a criminal offence in the course of these proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ige 1 ei v&auml;lista riigi vastutust kohtu poolt &otilde;igusem&otilde;istmisega mitteseotud tegevusega tekitatud kahju eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subsection (1) of this section does not preclude state liability for damage caused by the acts of a court which are not related to administration of justice. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igusp&auml;rase haldusakti v&otilde;i toiminguga tekitatud kahju </eesti>
<inglise>Damage caused by lawful administrative act or measure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda &otilde;igusp&auml;rase, kuid tema p&otilde;hi&otilde;igusi v&otilde;i -vabadusi erakordselt piirava haldusakti v&otilde;i halduse toiminguga tekitatud varalise kahju h&uuml;vitamist &otilde;iglases ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may claim compensation, to a fair extent, for proprietary damage caused by a lawful administrative act or measure which in an extraordinary manner restricts the fundamental rights or freedoms of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti, ei saa k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud h&uuml;vitist n&otilde;uda ulatuses, milles: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unless otherwise provided by law, compensation specified in subsection (1) of this section cannot be claimed to the extent where: </inglise>
<eesti>1) p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste v&otilde;i -vabaduste piiramise p&otilde;hjustas isik ise v&otilde;i see toimus tema huvides; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the restriction of fundamental rights or freedoms was caused by the person or the restriction was in the interests of the person; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isikute eriline kohtlemine on ette n&auml;htud seadusega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) special treatment of persons is prescribed by law; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isikul on h&uuml;vitist v&otilde;imalik saada mujalt, sealhulgas kindlustuselt; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the person can receive compensation from elsewhere, including from insurance; </inglise>
<eesti>4) h&uuml;vitise maksmise k&uuml;simus on reguleeritud muude seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the issue of payment of compensation is regulated by other Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) H&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramisel arvestatakse kasu, mida p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste v&otilde;i -vabaduste piiramine avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjale v&otilde;i avalikele huvidele kaasa t&otilde;i, piiramise raskust, kahju tekkimise etten&auml;gematust ja muid olulisi asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon grant of compensation, the benefit gained by the public authority or advance in public interests which is a result of the restriction of fundamental rights and freedoms, gravity of the restriction, the unforeseeability of damage and other relevant circumstances shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti>3. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju h&uuml;vitamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for compensation for damage </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse v&otilde;i kaebuse esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Filing of application or action </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks v&otilde;ib esitada taotluse kahju tekitanud haldusorganile v&otilde;i kaebuse halduskohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order for compensation for damage to be granted, an application may be submitted to the administrative authority which caused the damage or an action may be filed with an administrative court. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlus kohtu poolt tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks esitatakse Justiitsministeeriumile. </eesti>
<inglise>Applications for compensation for damage caused by courts shall be submitted to the Ministry of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kahju tekitamisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 12 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul esitatakse taotlus haldusorganile, kes kahju tekitanud f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i era&otilde;iguslikule juriidilisele isikule andis volitused avalike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If damage is caused in a case specified in subsection 12 (3) of this Act, the application shall be submitted to the administrative authority which authorised the natural person or private law legal person who caused the damage to perform public duties. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui volitused tulenevad vahetult seadusest, esitatakse taotlus f&uuml;&uuml;silise v&otilde;i era&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku &uuml;le riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostavale haldusorganile. </eesti>
<inglise>If authority arises expressly from law, the application shall be submitted to the administrative authority exercising state supervision over the natural person or private law legal person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotlus v&otilde;i kaebus tuleb esitada kolme aasta jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, millal kannatanu kahjust ja selle p&otilde;hjustanud isikust teada sai v&otilde;i pidi teada saama, s&otilde;ltumata teada saamisest aga 10 aasta jooksul kahju tekitamisest v&otilde;i selle p&otilde;hjustanud s&uuml;ndmusest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application or action shall be filed within three years as of the date on which the injured party became aware or should have become aware of the damage and of the person who caused it, but not later than within ten years as of the causing of damage or the event which caused the damage regardless of whether the injured party became aware of the damage and of the person who caused it. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotluse l&auml;bivaatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Review of applications </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Haldusorgan peab taotluse lahendama kahe kuu jooksul selle n&otilde;uetekohasest esitamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An administrative authority is required to adjudicate an application within two months as of the submission thereof as required. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui haldusorgan j&auml;tab kahju h&uuml;vitamise taotluse rahuldamata v&otilde;i t&auml;htaegselt lahendamata v&otilde;i kui kannatanu ei n&otilde;ustu h&uuml;vitise suuruse v&otilde;i viisiga, v&otilde;ib kannatanu 30 p&auml;eva jooksul esitada halduskohtule kaebuse h&uuml;vitise v&auml;ljam&otilde;istmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an administrative authority denies an application for compensation for damage or fails to adjudicate an application during the term or if the injured party does not agree to the amount or manner of compensation, the injured party may file an action with an administrative court within thirty days for the order of payment of compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>4. jagu </eesti>
<inglise>Division 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Regress </eesti>
<inglise>Recourse </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Regressi alused </eesti>
<inglise>Bases for recourse </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevast peat&uuml;kist tulenevalt kahju h&uuml;vitanud avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja v&otilde;ib esitada regressin&otilde;ude k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 12 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud isiku vastu, kelle &otilde;igusvastase tegevuse tulemusena kahju tekkis, v&otilde;i avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja vastu, kelle eest solidaarvastutuse alusel kahju h&uuml;vitati. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A public authority who compensates for damage on the basis of this Chapter may file a claim of recourse against a person specified in subsections 12 (2) and (3) of this Act whose unlawful activities resulted in the occurrence of damage, or against a public authority for whom damage was compensated for on the basis of solidary liability. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) H&uuml;vitist v&auml;hendatakse, kui regressin&otilde;ude t&auml;ielik rahuldamine oleks eba&otilde;iglane, arvestades avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja poolt antud korraldusi ja juhiseid ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 13 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud asjaolusid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Compensation is reduced if satisfying a claim of recourse in full would be unfair taking into account orders and instructions issued by the public authority and considering circumstances specified in subsection 13 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 12 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud isik vastutab avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja ees &uuml;ksnes s&uuml;&uuml;liselt kahju p&otilde;hjustamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person specified in subsection 12 (2) of this Act is liable to a public authority only if damage was caused wrongfully. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise n&otilde;udmise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for claim of compensation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Regressin&otilde;ude alusel h&uuml;vitise saamiseks teeb avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja isikule kirjaliku ettepaneku, n&auml;idates &auml;ra kahju h&uuml;vitamise ulatuse, korra ja t&auml;htaja ning h&uuml;vitise n&otilde;udmise aluseks olevad asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to receive compensation on the basis of a claim of recourse, a public authority shall make a written proposal to a person, specifying the extent of, procedure for and the term of compensation for damage and the circumstances which are the basis for claiming compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>Isik vastab ettepanekule kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>The person shall respond to the proposal in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettepaneku v&otilde;ib teha kolme kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, millal avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja regressin&otilde;ude aluseks olevatest asjaoludest teada sai v&otilde;i pidi teada saama, s&otilde;ltumata teada saamisest aga kolme aasta jooksul kahju tekitamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A proposal may be made within three months as of the date when the public authority became or should have become aware of the circumstances which are the basis of the claim of recourse, but not later than within three years as of the causing of damage regardless of whether or not the public authority became aware of the circumstances. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud t&auml;htaeg ei hakka kulgema enne riigi poolt kannatanule kahju h&uuml;vitamise otsustamist v&otilde;i riigilt kannatanu kasuks h&uuml;vitise v&auml;ljam&otilde;istmist. </eesti>
<inglise>The said term shall not commence before payment of compensation for damage to the injured party by the state is decided or the state is ordered to pay compensation to the injured party. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettepanekule vastamiseks tuleb isikule anda aega v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The person shall be given at least two weeks to respond to the proposal. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui isik ei ole &otilde;igeaegselt ettepanekule vastanud, keeldub kahju h&uuml;vitamisest v&otilde;i ei ole ettepanekus n&auml;idatud t&auml;htajaks kahju h&uuml;vitanud, on avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjal &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda h&uuml;vitise v&auml;ljam&otilde;istmiseks halduskohtusse 30 p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esolevas l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud asjaolude ilmnemisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a person fails to respond to the proposal in a timely manner, refuses to compensate for damage or fails to compensate for damage during the term indicated in the proposal, the public authority has the right of recourse to an administrative court, within thirty days as of the occurrence of the circumstances provided for in this subsection, for the order of payment of compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjat esindab regressin&otilde;ude esitamisel haldusorgan, kes otsustas kahju h&uuml;vitamise kannatanule. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon filing of a claim of recourse, the public authority shall be represented by the administrative authority which decided the compensation for damage to the injured party. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Regressi erijuhud </eesti>
<inglise>Special cases of recourse </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik vastutab avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja ees avaliku teenistuse seaduses (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 ja 276; 2000, 25, 144 ja 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 ja 18; 17, 78; 42, 233) s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official is liable to a public authority on the bases and pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Public Service Act (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 and 276; 2000, 25, 144 and 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 and 18; 17, 78; 42, 233). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isik, kes tekitas kahju tema ja avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja vahelise era&otilde;igussuhte alusel tegutsedes, vastutab avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja ees &uuml;ksnes era&otilde;iguses s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person who causes damage acting on the basis of a private law relationship between the person and a public authority is liable to the public authority only on the bases provided by private law. </inglise>
