<eesti>Alusetu rikastumine avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes </eesti>
<inglise>Unjust enrichment in public law relationships </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isik v&otilde;ib avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjalt n&otilde;uda &otilde;igusliku aluseta avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes &uuml;leantud asja v&otilde;i raha tagastamist, kui seadus ei s&auml;testa teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person may request a public authority to return a thing or money transferred without legal basis in a public law relationship unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui alusetult saadud asja tagastamine on v&otilde;imatu v&otilde;i seotud &uuml;lem&auml;&auml;raste kuludega, v&otilde;ib &otilde;igustatud isik n&otilde;uda asja v&auml;&auml;rtuse h&uuml;vitamist rahas. </eesti>
<inglise>If the return of a thing received without legal basis is not possible or involves excessive costs, the entitled person may request compensation for the value of the thing in money. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui k&auml;esoleva seadusega ei ole reguleeritud teisiti ja see ei ole vastuolus avalik-&otilde;igusliku suhte olemusega, kohaldatakse avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes toimunud alusetu rikastumise korral era&otilde;iguse s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unless otherwise regulated by this Act and if it is not in conflict with the nature of the public law relationship, the provisions of private law apply to unjust enrichment in a public law relationship. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja v&otilde;ib isikult n&otilde;uda &otilde;igusliku aluseta avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes &uuml;leantud asja v&otilde;i raha tagastamist era&otilde;iguses s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A public authority may request from a person the return of a thing or money transferred without legal basis in a public law relationship on the bases and pursuant to the procedure provided by private law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Intress ja asjast saadud kasu </eesti>
<inglise>Interest and benefit received from thing </inglise>
<eesti>Lisaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 22 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatule v&otilde;ib isik n&otilde;uda avaliku v&otilde;imu kandjalt: </eesti>
<inglise>In addition to the provisions of subsection 22 (1) of this Act, a person may request from a public authority: </inglise>
<eesti>1) intressi alusetult saadud raha eest kuus protsenti aastas; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an interest of 6 per cent per year for money received without legal basis; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asja v&otilde;&otilde;randamisest ja asja kasutamisest saadud kasu &uuml;leandmist. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the handing over of gains received from the transfer and use of the thing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>N&otilde;ude &uuml;le otsustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Deciding on claims </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalik-&otilde;iguslikus suhtes alusetust rikastumisest tuleneva n&otilde;ude &uuml;le otsustab asja v&otilde;i raha saanud haldusorgan haldusaktiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Claims arising from unjust enrichment in public law relationships shall be decided on, by an administrative act, by the administrative authority which received the thing or money. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldusaktis m&auml;rgitakse &auml;ra tagastamise v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitamise viis ja ulatus. </eesti>
<inglise>The manner and extent of the return or compensation shall be indicated in the administrative act. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja omandis oleva kinnisasja v&otilde;i muu registrisse kantud asja tagastamisel &otilde;igustatud isikule tehakse omandi&otilde;iguse &uuml;lemineku kohta kinnistusraamatusse v&otilde;i muusse registrisse kanne haldusakti ja avaliku v&otilde;imu kandja notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud avalduse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the return to an entitled person of an immovable or another thing entered in a register which is in the possession of a public authority, an entry concerning the transfer of ownership shall be made in the land register or another register on the basis of the administrative act and a notarised application from the public authority. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Taotlus v&otilde;i kaebus tuleb esitada kolme aasta jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, millal &otilde;igustatud isik n&otilde;udest teada sai v&otilde;i pidi teada saama, s&otilde;ltumata teada saamisest aga 10 aasta jooksul n&otilde;ude tekkimisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application or action shall be filed within three years as of the date on which the entitled person became aware or should have become aware of the claim, but not later than within ten years as of the creation of the claim regardless of whether or not the entitled person became aware of the claim. </inglise>
