<eesti>Ametniku varaline vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Proprietary liability of officials </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik on kohustatud h&uuml;vitama riigile v&otilde;i kohalikule omavalitsus&uuml;ksusele, kelle asutuses ta kahju tekitamise ajal t&ouml;&ouml;tas, s&uuml;&uuml;liselt teenistuskohustuse rikkumisega tekitatud kahju. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official is required to compensate for damage, wrongfully caused as a result of a breach of duties, to the state or local government in whose agency the official was employed at the time the damage was caused. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigile v&otilde;i kohalikule omavalitsus&uuml;ksusele ametniku poolt tekitatud kahjuks on ka riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse poolt makstud h&uuml;vitis ametniku teenistuskohustuse rikkumisega kolmandale isikule tekitatud kahju eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Compensation paid by the state or local government for damage caused to a third party as a result of a breach of duties of an official is deemed to be damage caused to the state or local government by the official. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mitme ametniku poolt kahju &uuml;hisel tekitamisel vastutab iga ametnik tema s&uuml;&uuml;le vastavas ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If damage is caused by several officials jointly, each official shall be liable to the extent corresponding to his or her fault. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) H&uuml;vitise suuruse m&auml;&auml;ramisel arvestatakse ametniku majanduslikku olukorda, kahju suurust ametniku palgaga v&otilde;rreldes, teenistuskohustuse iseloomust tulenevat riski kahju tekkimiseks, teenistusstaa&zcaron;ist objektiivselt tulenevat kogemuste puudumist, ametnikule antud teenistusalaseid korraldusi ja juhiseid, samuti muid asjaolusid, millest tulenevalt kahju t&auml;ielik h&uuml;vitamine ametniku poolt oleks eba&otilde;iglane. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The amount of compensation is determined on the basis of the economic situation of the official, the extent of damage as compared to the salary of the official, the assessment of the risk of causing damage arising from the nature of duties, lack of experience objectively arising from the length of service, the service-related orders and instructions issued to the official, and other circumstances which would render compensation for damage by the official in full unfair. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui kahju pole tekitatud tahtlikult, ei tohi n&otilde;utav h&uuml;vitis &uuml;letada ametniku kuuekordset ametipalga ja lisatasude summat. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If damage was not caused intentionally, the compensation shall not exceed six times the amount of the total of salary and additional remuneration of the official. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 89 (2). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 89 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>Kahju h&uuml;vitamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for compensation for damage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks teeb ametniku ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omav isik ametnikule kirjaliku ettepaneku, n&auml;idates &auml;ra kahju h&uuml;vitamise ulatuse, korra ja t&auml;htaja ning h&uuml;vitise n&otilde;udmise aluseks olevad asjaolud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order for compensation for damage to be granted, the person with authority to appoint an official makes a written proposal to the official, specifying the extent of, procedure for and the term of compensation for damage and the circumstances which are the basis of claiming compensation. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnik vastab ettepanekule kirjalikult, n&auml;idates &auml;ra, kas ta kohustub kahju h&uuml;vitama v&otilde;i keeldub sellest. </eesti>
<inglise>The official shall respond to the proposal in writing, indicating whether he or she undertakes to compensate for damage or refuses to do so. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettepaneku v&otilde;ib teha kolme kuu jooksul, arvates p&auml;evast, millal ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omav isik n&otilde;ude aluseks olevatest asjaoludest teada sai v&otilde;i pidi teada saama, kuid mitte hiljem, kui kolme aasta jooksul kahju tekitamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A proposal may be made within three months as of the date when the person with appointment authority became or should have become aware of the circumstances which are the basis of the claim but not later than within three years as of the causing of damage. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettepanekule vastamiseks tuleb ametnikule anda aega v&auml;hemalt kaks n&auml;dalat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official shall be given at least two weeks to respond to the proposal. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui ametnik ei ole &otilde;igeaegselt ettepanekule vastanud, keeldub kahju h&uuml;vitamisest v&otilde;i ei ole ettepanekus n&auml;idatud t&auml;htajaks kahju h&uuml;vitanud, m&otilde;istab ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igust omava isiku kaebuse alusel ametnikult h&uuml;vitise v&auml;lja halduskohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an official fails to respond to the proposal on time, refuses to compensate for damage or fails to compensate for damage during the term indicated in the proposal, the official shall be ordered by an administrative court to pay compensation on the basis of an appeal filed by the person with appointment authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlus tuleb halduskohtule esitada 30 p&auml;eva jooksul kaebuse esitamise &otilde;iguse tekkimisest arvates." </eesti>
<inglise>The application shall be filed with the administrative court within thirty days after the right to file an action arises." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
